newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Jakarta call money falls to 7.0/8.0 percent.
newsitem.headline: Jakarta call money falls to 7.0/8.0 percent.

text.p: Jakarta call money fell to 7.0/8.0 percent on Monday morning from around 8.0/9.0 percent at the opening amid flush market liquidity, dealers said.
One foreign bank dealer said the central bank's early injection of 2.219 trillion rupiah had caused an oversupply in the slow market.
Dealers said one-week money was also on the downtrend as liquidity was likely to remain sufficient in the near term.
One-week money was last quoted at 11.75/12.00, two at 13.00/13.25, while one and six-month money were last quoted at 13.50/13.62 and 14.75/15.00 respectively.
The average overnight interbank rate was at 10.40 on Friday compared with 10.21 percent on Thursday.
